C%20pumped%20in%20Rs%20664%20crore%20in%20political%20funding%20since%20May%202019%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%20564%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20purchased%20by%20five%20firms%20part%20of%20his%20group%20of%20companies%20and%20Rs%20100%20crore%20through%20an%20electoral%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20five%20companies%20that%20spent%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20Haldia%20Energy%20Ltd.%20purchased%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20377%20crore%2C%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure%20Limited%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20115%20crore%2C%20Philips%20Carbon%20Black%20Ltd.%20spent%20Rs.%2035%20crore%2C%20Crescent%20Power%20Ltd.%20spent%20Rs%2034%20crore%20and%20RPSG%20Ventures%20Ltd.%20spent%20Rs%203%20crore%20on%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20data%20revealed%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI)%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20instructions%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20companies%20also%20contributed%20Rs%2010%20crore%20in%202019%2C%20Rs%2065%20crore%20in%202021%20and%20Rs%2025%20crore%20in%202022%20through%20the%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20which%20gave%20the%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20the%20funds%20it%20raised%20from%20corporates%20and%20individuals%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20data%20made%20public%20by%20the%20ECI%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%2C%20he%20has%20emerged%20as%20among%20the%20top%20political%20funders%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20between%20trusts%20and%20bonds%20is%20that%20the%20payments%20made%20to%20the%20trust%20are%20required%20to%20be%20declared%20and%20the%20information%20becomes%20public%2C%20whereas%20the%20bonds%20were%20meant%20to%20remain%20secret%20until%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20February%20scrapped%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%2218%20of%2019%20Firms%20Marked%20'High-Risk'%20by%20Finance%20Ministry%20That%20Bought%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Went%20Off%20Subsequent%20List%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2F18-of-19-firms-marked-high-risk-by-finance-ministry-that-bought-electoral-bonds-went-off-future-list%5C%22%3E18%20of%2019%20Firms%20Marked%20%E2%80%98High-Risk%E2%80%99%20by%20Finance%20Ministry%20That%20Bought%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Went%20Off%20Subsequent%20List%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fprofile%2Fsanjiv-goenka%2F%3Fsh%3D2a27c5b66301%5C%22%3ESanjiv%20Goenka%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20one%20of%20Kolkata%E2%80%99s%20wealthiest%20persons%2C%20and%20his%20group%20has%20business%20footprints%20in%20power%2C%20consumer%20and%20retail%2C%20carbon%20black%2C%20IT-enabled%20services%2C%20media%20and%20entertainment%2C%20sports%2C%20and%20education%20sectors.%20His%20CESC%20Ltd%20supplies%20power%20to%20Kolkata%2C%20the%20biggest%20city%20in%20eastern%20India%2C%20while%20he%20also%20owns%20the%20Indian%20Premiere%20League%20(IPL)%20cricket%20team%20Lucknow%20Super%20Giants%20and%20the%20Indian%20Super%20League%20(ISL)%20football%20club%20Mohun%20Bagan%20Super%20Giants.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%2C%20just%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbusiness%2Ftop-electoral-bond-purchasers-include-some-companies-that-were-raided-or-under-the-scanner%5C%22%3Eseveral%20other%20political%20donors%20through%20electoral%20bonds%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20has%20been%20facing%20probes%20by%20central%20investigative%20agencies%20like%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20and%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigations%20(CBI).%20Notably%2C%20a%20Rs%2040%20crore%20purchase%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20came%20a%20month%20after%20the%20CBI%20started%20an%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20spending%20by%20Goenka%E2%80%99s%20companies%20happened%20during%20March-April%202021%2C%20the%20time%20of%20the%20high-stakes%20West%20Bengal%20assembly%20election.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20elections%20happened%20in%20south%20India%E2%80%99s%20Kerala%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20northeast%20India%E2%80%99s%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202021%2C%20the%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.assettype.com%2Fnationalherald%2F2021-12%2F65a780e3-35b8-49a3-b462-b4b78517b7f8%2FCRofPrudentElectoralTrust.pdf%5C%22%3Egave%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Rs%2055%20crore%20to%20the%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust.%20Haldia%20Energy%20India%20Ltd%20gave%20Rs%2025%20crore%20on%20March%2015%2C%20Phillips%20Carbon%20Black%20gave%20Rs%2020%20crore%20on%20March%2016%2C%20Crescent%20Power%20Limited%20gave%20Rs%205%20crore%20on%20March%2019%20and%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure%20gave%20Rs%205%20crore%20on%20March%2025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20Rs%20245.72%20crore%20the%20Trust%20raised%20from%20corporates%20and%20individuals%20during%202020-21%2C%20a%20whopping%20Rs%20209%20crore%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%2C%20the%20key%20petitioner%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20case%20against%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fcontent%2Ffirm-facing-ed-probe-rs-400-cr-fraud-donated-rs-100-cr-electoral-trust-bjp-biggest-taker%5C%22%3Eshowed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202022.%20Goenka%E2%80%99s%20companies%20accounted%20for%2022.4%25%20of%20what%20the%20Trust%20raised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20Rs%2055%20crore%20to%20the%20Trust%2C%20the%20group%20purchased%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2067%20crore%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20Haldia%20bought%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2020%20crore%20on%20April%206%20and%20Rs%2015%20crore%20on%20April%208%2C%20Philips%20spent%20Rs%2020%20crore%20on%20April%203%20and%20Rs%2010%20crore%20on%20April%208%2C%20and%20Crescent%20spent%20Rs%202%20crore%20on%20April%206%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20group%20cumulatively%20spent%20Rs%20122%20crore%20in%20political%20funding%20during%20the%20assembly%20election%20months%20of%20March-April%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20blow%2C%20the%202021%20election%20was%20almost%20a%20do-or-die%20battle%20for%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC).%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20had%20high%20hopes%20in%20West%20Bengal%20and%20Assam%20and%20was%20also%20pushing%20hard%20to%20increase%20its%20footprints%20in%20the%20southern%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20was%20the%20BJP%20that%20benefited%20from%20the%20Goenka%20group%E2%80%99s%20funding%20through%20electoral%20trusts%2C%20it%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20who%20benefitted%20from%20the%20companies%E2%80%99%20spending%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20for%20which%20one%20would%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20serial%20numbers%20of%20bond%20purchaser%20and%20recipient%20to%20be%20made%20public%20by%20the%20ECI%20and%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20(SBI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20claims%20to%20have%20a%20%246%20billion%20asset%20base%20and%20%244%20billion%20revenue%2C%20and%20describes%20itself%20as%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20fastest%20growing%20conglomerates%20with%20a%20significant%20global%20presence%E2%80%9D.%20Though%20based%20in%20Bengal%2C%20the%20group%20has%20a%20growing%20interest%20in%20states%20like%20Rajasthan%20and%20Gujarat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20renewables%20business%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rpsg.in%2Fbusiness%2Frb%5C%22%3Eincludes%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0156MW%20of%20wind%20power%20plants%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Gujarat%20and%2027MW%20of%20solar%20power%20plants%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20In%20January%202024%2C%20the%20group%E2%80%99s%20CESC%20Projects%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessworld.in%2Farticle%2FRP-Sanjiv-Goenka-Group-s-CESC-Projects-Gets-10-500-MT-Green-Hydrogen-Plant-Contract%2F09-01-2024-505291%2F%5C%22%3Esecured%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20contract%20of%20a%20500%20MT%20Green%20Hydrogen%20Plant%20Contract%2C%20given%20by%20the%20Solar%20Energy%20Corporation%20of%20India%20(SECI)%2C%20a%20public%20sector%20enterprise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20it%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenergy.economictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Frenewable%2Frp-sanjiv-goenka-group-to-explore-ne-states-for-renewable-energy-project%2F107867320%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20company%20was%20looking%20to%20acquire%20over%2050%2C000%20acres%20of%20land%20in%20Rajasthan%20and%20Gujarat%20to%20fuel%20its%203%20GW%20green%20energy%20dream%20with%20solar%20power%2C%20beside%20planning%20to%20expand%20operations%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20northeastern%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Top%20Five%20Political%20Parties%20Saw%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Fortunes%20Turning%20With%20Election%20Wins%20and%20Losses%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftop-five-political-parties-saw-electoral-bonds-fortunes-turning-with-election-wins-and-losses%5C%22%3ETop%20Five%20Political%20Parties%20Saw%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Fortunes%20Turning%20With%20Election%20Wins%20and%20Losses%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20March-April%202021%20funding%20was%20a%20big%20leap%20in%20the%20RP%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20group%E2%80%99s%20political%20funding%20pattern%2C%20at%20least%20through%20formal%20channels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20started%20their%20funding%20activities%20on%20May%207%2C%202019%2C%20amidst%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20with%20Rs%2020%20crore%20from%20Haldia%20and%20Philips%20in%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20Rs%2010%20crore%20from%20Haldia%20Energy%20to%20the%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%20on%20May%2013%2C%202019.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20the%20group%20donated%20Rs%201%20crore%20in%20October%202019%2C%20Rs%206%20crore%20on%20January%2018%2C%202020%2C%20and%20Rs%2015%20crore%20on%20October%2019%2C%202020%2C%20through%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%202017-18%20the%20company%20was%20facing%20a%20probe%20by%20the%20ED%2C%20which%20first%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fdata%2Fannouncements%2Fbse%2F06112017%2F2f4a76af-70dd-437e-96bd-da2368369368.PDF%5C%22%3Eraided%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20group%E2%80%99s%20music%20venture%20Saregama%E2%80%99s%20premises%20both%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Kolkata%20in%20November%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20March-April%202021%20funding%2C%20the%20big%20chunks%20came%20in%20October%202022%2C%20October%202023%20and%20January%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20timings%20are%20interesting.%20In%20September%202022%2C%20the%20CBI%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frpg-industrial-group-faces-corruption-case-in-1990s-coal-block-allocation-3362364%5C%22%3Estarted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0an%20investigation%20against%20the%20company%20on%20the%20charge%20of%20involvement%20in%20the%20allocations%20of%20coal%20blocks%20in%20the%20past.%20October%202022%20saw%20spending%20of%20Rs%2040%20crore%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2015%20crore%20from%20Crescent%2C%20and%20Rs%2025%20crore%20from%20Dhariwal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOctober%202023%20was%20another%20Rs%2040%20crore%20month%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2025%20crore%20from%20Haldia%20Energies%20and%20Rs%2015%20crore%20from%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure.%20It%20was%20also%20the%20month%20before%20elections%20in%20five%20states%20of%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Telangana%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Mizoram.%20The%20TMC%2C%20West%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2C%20did%20not%20have%20any%20interest%20in%20these%20elections%2C%20but%20the%20BJP%20and%20the%20Congress%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202023%2C%20Rs%2015%20crore%20was%20spent%20through%20bonds%20in%20April%2C%20July%20and%20October%20each%20from%20Dhariwal%20Infrastructure.%20Then%2C%20in%20January%202024%2C%20Haldia%20Energy%20spent%20Rs%2045%20crore%20on%20buying%20electoral%20bonds.%20The%20elections%20were%20again%20around%20the%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2017%20last%20year%2C%20Sanjiv%20Goenka%20said%20at%20the%20India%20Today%20Conclave%20that%20%E2%80%9CModi%20ji%20had%20taught%20the%20world%20to%20respect%20India%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20the%20world%20around%20us%20is%20crumbling%2C%20India%20is%20actually%20standing%20up%20and%20doing%20well.%20A%20few%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20you%20went%20outside%2C%20nobody%20gave%20Indians%20any%20respect.%20Today%2C%20when%20you%20go%20outside%20and%20say%20%E2%80%98I%20am%20from%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20you%20are%20given%20respect.%20I%20think%20Modi%20ji%20has%20taught%20the%20world%20to%20respect%20India%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Frpsg-group-chairman-sanjiv-goenka-prime-minister-narendra-modi-world-respect-india-2347959-2023-03-17%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710653723000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F17110325%2FGoenka-collage.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkolkata-billionaire-sanjiv-goenkas-companies-spent-rs-664-crore-in-electoral-bonds-and-trusts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20group%2C%20which%20faced%20both%20ED%20and%20CBI%20investigations%2C%20spent%20Rs%20122%20crore%20through%20bonds%20and%20electoral%20trusts%20during%20the%202021%20Bengal%20elections.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fkolkata-billionaire-sanjiv-goenkas-companies-spent-rs-664-crore-in-electoral-bonds-and-trusts%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russia%20says%20it%20repelled%20multiple%20drone%20attacks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710653657000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FF3B0%2Fproduction%2F_132948326_gettyimages-1143479326.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-685