Fa%3E%2C%20have%20shown%2C%20many%20peoples%20actually%20experience%20the%20breakdown%20of%20their%20encompassing%20%E2%80%98civilisation%E2%80%99%E2%80%94that%20moves%20wealth%20and%20power%20away%20from%20the%20imperial%20peripheries%20toward%20its%20centre%E2%80%94as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F3quarksdaily.com%2F3quarksdaily%2F2022%2F04%2Fthis-is-not-the-zombie-apocalypse.html%5C%22%3Eliberation%20at%20least%20as%20much%20as%20a%20disaster%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20the%20industrial%20world%20disintegrates%E2%80%94under%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20collapsing%20ecosystems%2C%20and%20other%20biophysical%20limits%20to%20its%20demands%20for%20ever-increasing%20energy%20and%20materials%E2%80%94alternative%20futures%20can%20arise.%20Diverse%20communities%20around%20the%20world%20can%20and%20will%20respond%20in%20ways%20that%20liberate%20them%20to%20practice%20bottom-up%20governance%20and%20mutual%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20stand%20on%20the%20cusp%20of%20a%20transition%20in%20the%20human%20enterprise%20no%20less%20profound%20than%20the%20one%20that%20took%20our%20ancient%20ancestors%20from%20lives%20of%20nomadic%20foraging%20to%20our%20modern%20age%20of%20industrial%20petro-capitalism%2C%20a%20transition%20that%E2%80%99s%20taken%20many%20hundreds%20of%20generations.%20That%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fthe-agricultural-revolution-an-alternate-telling%5C%22%3Etransition%20changed%20our%20stories%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20ourselves%20and%20our%20world%2C%20giving%20birth%20to%20entirely%20new%20forms%20of%20religion%2C%20social%20and%20political%20structures%2C%20living%20arrangements%2C%20dietary%20norms%2C%20frames%20of%20identity.%20And%20so%20must%20we%20open%20ourselves%20to%20a%20human%20cultural%20future%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20hundreds%20of%20generations%20to%20drift%20through%20profound%20sociopolitical%20changes%2C%20even%20though%2C%20like%20our%20ancestors%2C%20we%20also%20can%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20our%20future%20world%20will%20look.%20Yet%20we%20must%20have%20%3Cem%3Eintention%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20change%20in%20some%20very%20particular%20ways%3A%20reduce%20excessive%20consumption%3B%20decrease%20ecological%20destruction%3B%20expand%20mutual-aid%20social%20constructs%20and%20local%20cooperation%3B%20phase%20out%20the%20mechanisms%20driving%20inequality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMake%20no%20mistake%3A%20this%20is%20not%20about%20reviving%20socialism%20or%20communism%20or%20any%20similarly%20growthist%2C%20power-centralising%20sociopolitical%20paradigms%20born%20of%20the%20Industrial%20Revolution.%20The%20restructuring%20that%E2%80%99s%20required%20in%20pursuing%20a%20goal%20of%20greater%20ecological%20balance%20falls%20outside%20the%20limited%20political%20frames%20of%20reference%20that%20constrain%20our%20modern%20imaginations.%20It%20is%20time%20to%20crack%20open%20our%20hearts%20and%20minds%20to%20understand%20something%20of%20our%20larger%20human%20potential.%20In%20this%20we%20have%20only%20the%20advantage%20of%20our%20historical%20perspective.%20We%20know%20something%20of%20where%20we%E2%80%99ve%20come%20from%20and%20where%20different%20choices%20can%20lead.%20We%20know%20also%20that%20very%20different%20ways%20of%20life%20are%20absolutely%20humanly%20possible%2C%20that%20many%20other%20ways%20of%20life%20can%20be%20perfectly%20desirable%E2%80%94even%20preferable%2C%20for%20many%E2%80%94compared%20to%20the%20way%20we%20live%20now.%20This%20is%20why%20growing%20numbers%20of%20heterodox%20economists%20and%20degrowth%20scholars%20are%20working%20outside%20the%20mainstream%2C%20shaking%20up%20the%20models%20used%20in%20their%20disciplines%20to%20align%20economic%20imperatives%20with%20ecological%20and%20biophysical%20limits%20and%20actual%20human%20social%20behaviour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScholars%20and%20activists%20from%20around%20the%20world%20are%20already%20coming%20together