rward%20but%20highly%20selective.%3Cp%3EGuy%20Snodgrass%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20in%20a%20lot%20of%20cases%20throughout%20my%20career%2C%20I%20was%20always%20attracted%20to%20trying%20to%20do%20the%20toughest%20things.%20And%20one%20of%20the%20pathways%20I%20could%20take%20after%20my%20time%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpilot-navy-topgun-what-its-like-daily-life-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENavy%20fighter%20pilot%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20to%20go%20through%20TOPGUN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20path%20I%20wanted%20to%20pursue%2C%20so%20I%20could%20try%20and%20reach%20that%20pinnacle%20of%20fighter%20pilots%20in%20naval%20aviation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20most%20demanding%20part%20of%20being%20a%20TOPGUN%20instructor%20for%20me%20wasn't%20the%20actual%20flying%2C%20like%20you%20see%20in%20%26quot%3BTop%20Gun%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BTop%20Gun%3A%20Maverick%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20lecture%20process%20as%20an%20instructor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20into%20TOPGUN%20is%20fairly%20straightforward.%20You've%20accumulated%20a%20body%20of%20work%20over%20your%20time%20in%20a%20flight%20squadron.%20You%20put%20in%20your%20application%2C%20you%20get%20letters%20of%20recommendations%20from%20pilots%20you've%20actively%20flown%20with%2C%20and%20typically%20your%20commanding%20officer%20from%20your%20unit%20will%20provide%20an%20independent%20evaluation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20an%20instructor%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20other%20side%20of%20this.%20Once%20you%20have%20all%20the%20applications%2C%20maybe%2030%20people%20for%20eight%20spots%2C%20there's%20this%20cascade%20%E2%80%94%20we%20call%20it%20the%20waterfall%20%E2%80%94%20in%20how%20people%20get%20chosen.%20You%20go%20through%20all%2030%20individuals%20and%20determine%20who%20are%20the%20few%2C%20usually%20maybe%20four%20or%20five%2C%20that%20we%20want%20to%20stay%20as%20instructors.%20The%20remainder%20of%20the%20pool%20can%20now%20be%20picked%20by%20other%20schools%2C%20so%20it%20kind%20of%20cascades%20down%20from%20TOPGUN.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20my%20case%2C%20I%20was%20selected%20to%20be%20an%20instructor.%20I%20went%20through%20the%20course%2C%20which%20today%20takes%20about%2012%20weeks%2C%20and%20at%20the%20conclusion%20of%20that%2C%20I%20was%20selected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20day%20in%20the%20life%20at%20TOPGUN%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Guy%20Snodgrass%20pic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef2b046080194819fea207%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223240%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20daily%20schedule%20is%20hectic%2C%20but%20debriefs%20after%20flights%20are%20the%20best%20time%20to%20learn%20and%20grow.%3Cp%3EGuy%20Snodgrass%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20typically%20an%20instructor%20at%20TOPGUN%20for%20two-and-a-half%2C%20maybe%20three%20years.%20You're%20flying%20every%20single%20day%2C%20Monday%20through%20Friday%2C%20and%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20twice%20a%20day.%20We'd%20get%20up%20early%2C%20around%204%3A30am%2C%20for%20our%20first%20brief%20at%20base%20around%205%3A30am%20to%206%3A00am.%20You%20have%20some%20time%20to%20relax%2C%20grab%20your%20gear%2C%20get%20into%20the%20cockpit%2C%20and%20then%20there's%20a%2030-minute%20period%20to%20get%20the%20jet%20started%20and%20get%20all%20the%20systems%20online%20and%20ready%20for%20take%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDepending%20on%20how%20dynamic%20your%20mission%20is%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20how%20aggressive%20and%20fast%20you're%20flying%20%E2%80%94%20you'll%20likely%20be%20airborne%20for%20about%20an%20hour%2C%20doing%20basic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-topgun-instructor-reveals-most-terrifying-moment-as-fighter-pilot-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflight%20maneuvers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20dogfighting%20you%20see%20in%20the%20%26quot%3BTop%20Gun%26quot%3B%20movies.%20A%20longer%20flying%20mission%20might%20be%20about%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20be%20dogfighting%20against%20an%20instructor%20or%20using%20the%20gun%20on%20the%20plane%20to%20strafe%20the%20target%20on%20the%20ground%20or%20drop%20bombs%20from%20high%20or%20low%20altitude%2C%20putting%20what%20you%20learn%20in%20the%20classroom%20towards%20practical%20application.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20you're%20becoming%20an%20expert%20in%20air-to-ground%20delivery%20and%20doing%20multiplane%20exercises%2C%20flying%20with%20one%20other%20plane%20to%20start%20and%20then%20you%20extend%20outwards%20with%20three%20other%20planes%20for%20pretty%20involved%20missions%2C%20dodging%20simulated%20surface-to-air%20missiles%2C%20fighting%20your%20way%20in%20and%20dropping%20weapons%2C%20then%20fighting%20your%20way%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20you%20get%20out%20of%20your%20gear%2C%20get%20some%20downtime%2C%20and%20then%20start%20the%20debrief.%20The%20debriefs%20are%20epic%20because%20they%20typically%20last%20anywhere%20from%20three-and-a-half%20to%20five%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20sessions%20can%20go%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%20because%20you're%20learning%20lessons%20from%20what%20you%20just%20flew.%20We%20would%20always%20say%20that%20the%20debrief%20is%20the%20most%20important%20because%20that's%20where%20you're%20learning%20your%20lessons%20and%20able%20to%20call%20them%20out%20in%20a%20real%2C%20tangible%20way%20so%20that%20you%20can%20apply%20them%20moving%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20debrief%2C%20you'll%20probably%20have%20an%20hour%20break%20and%20then%20do%20another%20flight%20and%20repeat%20the%20cycle.%20You%20typically%20head%20home%20around%2010%3A00%20pm%2C%20maybe%2010%3A30%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20they%20don't%20show%20in%20the%20movies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221311%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Guy%20Snodgrass%20pic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef2b326080194819fea21d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22742%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBoth%20%26quot%3BTop%20Gun%26quot%3B%20movies%20have%20their%20Hollywood%20magic%2C%20but%20they're%20surprisingly%20realistic.%20%3Cp%3EGuy%20Snodgrass%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20instructor%2C%20you%20go%20through%20the%20entirety%20of%20the%20process%2C%20and%20after%20everyone%20else%20finishes%20training%20and%20graduates%2C%20you%20stay%20and%20become%20a%20subject%20matter%20expert%20for%20some%20element%20of%20teachings%20at%20TOPGUN.%20Mine%20was%20air-to-air%20mission%20planning%2C%20so%20being%20in%20charge%20of%20long-range%20aerial%20combat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20you%20have%20six%20months%20to%20prepare%2C%20study%2C%20and%20practice%20to%20give%20this%20lecture%20on%20your%20area.%20You%20get%20eight%20practice%20lessons%20to%20receive%20feedback.%20In%20my%20case%2C%20it%20was%20a%20four-and-a-half%20hour%20long%20lecture%2C%20hundreds%20of%20presentation%20slides%2C%20and%20it%20had%20to%20be%20completely%20from%20memory.%20They%20don't%20let%20you%20look%20at%20your%20slides%2C%20and%20you%20can't%20use%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20biggest%20thing%2C%20the%20most%20demanding%20part%20for%20me%20wasn't%20the%20actual%20flying%2C%20but%20the%20lecture%20process%20and%20being%20able%20to%20do%20it%20completely%20from%20memory.%20But%20once%20I%20passed%20that%2C%20I%20was%20a%20fully%20qualified%20instructor%20and%20continued%20to%20learn%20and%20instruct%20throughout%20the%20remainder%20of%20my%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223888%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Guy%20Snodgrass%20pic%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ef2b7090413ab8e1db6302%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETeaching%20and%20leading%20your%20subject%20matter%20area%20lecture%20is%20the%20most%20difficult%20part%2C%20Snodgrass%20said.%3Cp%3EGuy%20Snodgrass%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20rewarding%20part%20of%20being%20a%20TOPGUN%20instructor%20was%20the%20personal%20relationships%20you%20form%20with%20the%20people%20around%20you%2C%20who%20are%20also%20dedicated%20to%20trying%20to%20achieve%20their%20best%20potential.%20There's%20a%20competitive%20air%20because%20everyone%20wants%20to%20try%20to%20be%20the%20best%2C%20but%20mostly%20there's%20camaraderie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20got%20to%20meet%20these%20students%20as%20they%20came%20through%2C%20interacting%20with%20the%20future%20of%20naval%20aviation%2C%20future%20leaders%20who%20are%20going%20to%20continue%20to%20grow%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20their%20career%20and%20assume%20positions%20of%20greater%20authority.%20As%20an%20instructor%2C%20you're%20having%20a%20real%20direct%20influence%20and%20ability%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftopgun-instructor-movies-flying-dogfighting-pretty-realistic-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710588601000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65f31757857f90b715228230%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftopgun-instructor-movies-flying-dogfighting-pretty-realistic-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22But%20there's%20also%20Hollywood%20magic.%20A%20fifth-generation%20fighter%20is%20going%20to%20smoke%20the%20F-14%20every%20single%20day%20and%20twice%20on%20Sunday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cpanella%40businessinsider.com%20(Chris%20Panella)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftopgun-instructor-movies-flying-dogfighting-pretty-realistic-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Astronomers%20discover%20a%20possible%20water%20world%20in%20the%20search%20for%20a%20habitable%20planet%2C%20report%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22815%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20the%20James%20Webb%20Space%20Telescope%20in%20space.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fecbb96f7540cd069787a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22429%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20James%20Webb%20space%20telescope.%3Cp%3Edima_zel%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EScientists%20say%20they%20observed%20a%20planet%20that%20may%20have%20an%20ocean-covered%20surface%2C%20the%20Guardian%20reported.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20observations%20were%20made%20using%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20space%20telescope.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20a%20Canadian%20research%20group%20said%20the%20planet%20is%20likely%20too%20hot%20for%20liquid%20water.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20say%20they%20have%20observed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Fexoplanet-catalog%2F7571%2Ftoi-270-d%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeptune-like%3C%2Fa%3E%20planet%20that%20could%20be%20covered%20by%20a%20deep-water%20ocean%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fscience%2F2024%2Fmar%2F08%2Fastronomers-detect-waterworld-with-a-boiling-ocean-in-deep-space%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR05Ygwpv64-frgfibQcglp6qAZy2Gy55rZ-gvltUB3SeATacVWvt9zGXoA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Guardian%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20team%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20in%20the%20UK%20said%20it%20had%20found%20evidence%20of%20water%20vapor%20and%20chemical%20signatures%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane%20on%20an%20exoplanet%20known%20as%20TOI-270%20d%2C%20which%20is%20around%2070%20light%20years%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20used%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20space%20telescope%20to%20make%20observations%20of%20the%20planet%2C%20which%20has%20twice%20the%20radius%20of%20Earth%20and%20a%20mass%20of%204.78%20Earths%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Fexoplanet-catalog%2F7571%2Ftoi-270-d%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENikku%20Madhusudhan%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20astrophysics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20who%20led%20the%20research%2C%20told%20the%20Guardian%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20ocean%20could%20be%20upwards%20of%20100%20degrees%20%5BCelsius%5D%20or%20more%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20with%20high%20atmospheric%20pressure%2C%20that%20ocean%20could%20still%20be%20liquid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20clear%20if%20it%20would%20be%20habitable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20planet%20is%20also%20tidally%20locked%2C%20meaning%20one%20side%20is%20left%20in%20constant%20darkness%20while%20the%20other%20faces%20its%20star%2C%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ocean%20would%20be%20extremely%20hot%20on%20the%20day%20side.%20The%20night%20side%20could%20potentially%20host%20habitable%20conditions%2C%26quot%3B%20Madhusudhan%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20liquid%20ocean%20is%20the%20preferred%20premise%20set%20out%20in%20a%20paper%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aanda.org%2Farticles%2Faa%2Ffull_html%2F2024%2F03%2Faa48238-23%2Faa48238-23.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAstronomy%20%26amp%3B%20Astrophysics%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20paper%20also%20notes%20the%20lack%20of%20ammonia%20on%20TOI-270%20d%2C%20which%20it%20said%20was%20%26quot%3Bconsistent%20with%20predictions%20for%20a%20Hycean%20world%20with%20a%20planet-wide%20ocean%26quot%3B%20under%20a%20hydrogen-rich%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20group%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2403.03325%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECanadian%20researchers%20who%20also%20observed%20TOI-270%20d%20have%20disputed%20the%20Cambridge%20team's%20claims.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they%20detected%20the%20same%20chemicals%20in%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere%2C%20one%20of%20the%20researchers%20told%20the%20Guardian%20that%20they%20believed%20the%20temperature%20was%20%26quot%3Btoo%20warm%20for%20water%20to%20be%20liquid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUniversit%C3%A9%20de%20Montr%C3%A9al%20Professor%20Bj%C3%B6rn%20Benneke%20said%20that%20surface%20temperatures%20on%20the%20exoplanet%20could%20be%20around%204%2C000%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20or%20around%207%2C200%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20this%20meant%20any%20water%20would%20be%20in%20a%20supercritical%20state%2C%20where%20%26quot%3Bit's%20almost%20like%20a%20thick%2C%20hot%20fluid.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22image%20of%20the%20colorful%20nebula%20in%20space%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F653fe053356802a56be791e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221307%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Crab%20Nebula%20photographed%20by%20NASA's%20James%20Webb%20Space%20Telescope.%3Cp%3ENASA%2C%20ESA%2C%20CSA%2C%20STScI%2C%20Tea%20Temim%20(Princeton%20University)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20James%20Webb%20telescope%20has%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20advancing%20the%20search%20for%20habitable%20planets%20beyond%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20telescope%20intercepts%20infrared%20light%20and%20directs%20it%20to%20scientific%20instruments%20where%20it%20can%20be%20recorded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20its%20main%20uses%20is%20to%20study%20the%20atmospheres%20of%20exoplanets%20to%20see%20whether%20they%20could%20support%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20that%20scientists%20look%20for%20in%20a%20potentially%20habitable%20planet%20is%20the%20presence%20of%20liquid%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20around%20a%20star%20where%20water%20can%20exist%20in%20a%20liquid%20state%20is%20called%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Ffaq%2F15%2Fwhat-is-the-habitable-zone-or-