saris%2C%20jewellery%2C%20etc.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98We%20are%20proud%20of%20our%20identity%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELed%20by%20Brijesh%2C%20the%20Sankalp%20Foundation%20involves%20around%20300%20people%20from%2072%20villages.%20This%20collective%20provides%20a%20platform%20for%20artists%20to%20learn%20about%20current%20trends%20and%20marketing%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20a%20beautiful%20chaos%20when%20multiple%20tribal%20communities%20come%20together%20to%20make%20the%20products.%20Although%20the%20communities%20have%20different%20traditions%2C%20their%20turmoil%20is%20mostly%20similar%2C%20which%20then%20becomes%20a%20point%20of%20unity.%20People%20that%20were%20once%20ashamed%20of%20their%20skills%20and%20identities%20are%20now%20proudly%20wearing%20and%20adorning%20them%20while%20making%20money%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Brijesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20close%20to%20nature%2C%20the%20Sankalp%20Foundation%20is%20happy%20to%20walk%20on%20the%20sustainability%20route.%20All%20their%20wooden%20products%20are%20made%20from%20fallen%3Cem%3E%20chikoo%3C%2Fem%3E%20twigs%20and%20branches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESustainability%20is%20also%20a%20winner%20in%20Brijesh%E2%80%99s%20neighbouring%20handloom%20stall%20belonging%20to%20the%20Bodo%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F331624%2Fassam-man-quits-his-job-to-make-sustainable-toys-that-represent-assams-tribes-and-culture%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etribes%20of%20Assam%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20our%20cotton%20clothes%20are%20made%20from%20natural%20colours%20that%20last%20forever%20and%20are%20also%20good%20for%20the%20skin.%20We%20make%20colours%20from%20turmeric%2C%20leaves%20from%20plants%20and%20a%20few%20vegetables%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Jaison%20Bhramo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJyotisankar%20Sahu%20of%20the%20Sabar%20tribe%20from%20Odish